[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(27) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Behold, we have forsaken.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The question betrayed the thoughts that had been working in the minds of the disciples, and of which, as was his wont, St. Peter made himself the spokesman. They had complied with their Master’s commands. What were they to have as the special reward to which they were thus entitled? It is obvious that in asking for that reward they showed that they had complied with the letter only, not with the spirit, of the command. They had not in the true sense of the word, denied themselves, though they had forsaken the earthly calling and the comforts of their home; and they were dwelling on what they had done, as in itself giving them a right to compensation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Matthew 19:27-28",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 19:27-28",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then answered Peter ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— With some warmth and confidence; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Behold, we have forsaken all ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— We have done what this youth, hopeful as he seemed, had not the resolution to do; for though indeed we had not much, we have left all the little that we had, and have at all adventures ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "followed thee ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with the sincerest zeal and affection. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "What shall we have therefore? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— It seems Peter was ready to think that their labour was lost, because they were to have no recompense on earth, and that his stewardship, the office which he supposed his Master had promised him under the metaphor of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the keys of the kingdom, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "was likely to be of little service to him. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jesus said, Ye which have followed me in the regeneration ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— During this time and state of things, in which men are to be regenerated and created anew by the gospel, and the earth is to be renewed in righteousness. Mr. Fleming paraphrases the verse thus: “You, my apostles, who have followed me in this new state of the church, which is to be brought to the birth when I am to ascend to heaven, shall be to the whole Christian Church what the twelve heads of the tribes were of old to the whole Jewish nation: my followers shall appeal to your decisions, as the rule of their faith and practice.” But, it seems, the expression, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εν τη παλιγγενεσια",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ought rather to be connected with what follows; the sense then will be, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "In the renovation, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "namely, the final renovation, or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "restitution of all things, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 3:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "when the Son of man shall sit on the throne of his glory — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Exalted above the highest angels of God, and presiding over and judging the assembled world; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ye also shall sit ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In the beginning of the judgment they shall ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "stand; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 5:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) Then, being absolved, they ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall sit ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with the Judge: (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 6:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " :) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "on twelve thrones ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— So our Lord promised, without expressing any condition: yet, as absolute as the words are, it is certain there is a condition implied, as in many scriptures where none is expressed. In consequence of this, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "these twelve ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "did not sit on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "those twelve thrones: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the throne of Judas another took, so that he never sat thereon. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Judging the twelve tribes of Israel ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Concurring joyfully with me in the sentence which will then be passed on the Jewish nation, and on all the professed members of my church, as they have been sincere or faithless in their profession, and in the observance of those laws which you, by authority from me, shall have given them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
